ASSEMBLY SOLAR I, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Assembly Solar I, LLC ("Assembly Solar I") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Assembly Solar I generating facility ("Assembly Solar I Facility").
The Assembly Solar I Facility is a solar generating facility located in Shiawassee County, Michigan. The Assembly Solar I Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Michigan Electric Transmission Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Assembly Solar I's revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Assembly Solar I Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Assembly Solar I's monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Assembly Solar I shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $375,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $31,250.00.
